1
00:00:00,170 --> 00:00:05,780
In this video we are going to add project reference between clean architecture layers.

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:12,050
It is crucial step to establish the correct dependencies between different layers of the application.

3
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:15,050
Let's understand layer dependencies.

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:22,340
As we said before, our domain and application layer responsible for business requirement without any

5
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:23,630
external dependencies.

6
00:00:23,930 --> 00:00:30,710
So we can think domain and application layer as a core layers and only application layer get referenced

7
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:34,850
from the domain layer and domain should not get any reference.

8
00:00:35,090 --> 00:00:41,630
And after that we have infrastructure layer which includes all external concerns and infrastructure

9
00:00:41,630 --> 00:00:48,260
layer should encapsulate these external dependencies like databases, edge systems, integrations and

10
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:48,830
so on.

11
00:00:48,830 --> 00:00:52,880
So these infrastructure layer could be replaced when needed.

12
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:57,260
And infrastructure layer should have application layer get referenced.

13
00:00:57,290 --> 00:01:04,670
That means we need to reference from the core layers into infrastructure layer in order to perform infrastructure

14
00:01:04,670 --> 00:01:05,960
works properly.

15
00:01:06,230 --> 00:01:12,920
And lastly, we have API layer as a presentation layer and this will need it both application and infrastructure

16
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:13,670
layers.

17
00:01:13,970 --> 00:01:19,850
As a result, we can say that domain layer, which is the ordering domain, has no dependency on other

18
00:01:19,850 --> 00:01:20,510
layers.

19
00:01:20,510 --> 00:01:27,050
And application layer, which is the ordinary application depends on the domain layer and infrastructure

20
00:01:27,050 --> 00:01:33,290
layer, which is the ordering infrastructure depends on the application layer for implementing interfaces

21
00:01:33,290 --> 00:01:39,560
and API layer, which is the ordering API depends on both application and infrastructure layer.

22
00:01:39,740 --> 00:01:43,820
Please open the Visual Studio and go to Ordering Application layer.

23
00:01:43,820 --> 00:01:49,310
In ordering application layer we are going to add project reference from the ordering domain.

24
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:55,580
Also, we will add a reference from the building blocks of the project in order to leverage skills,

25
00:01:55,580 --> 00:01:59,990
abstractions and other shared functionalities into ordering microservices.

26
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:05,330
For that purpose, I am going to come to ordering application, right click dependencies, Add Project

27
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:10,910
Reference and in here I am going to select Building Blocks and also ordering domain.

28
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:12,770
And click the okay button.

29
00:02:13,070 --> 00:02:17,660
And you can confirm in the Ordering application project file and save this file.

30
00:02:17,660 --> 00:02:19,730
See that these item group added.

31
00:02:19,730 --> 00:02:23,360
And two project is adding reference into ordering application.

32
00:02:23,690 --> 00:02:27,050
After that we can go to the ordering infrastructure.

33
00:02:27,140 --> 00:02:32,900
In Ordering infrastructure layer, we will add a project reference from the ordering application and

34
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:37,580
implement its interface and use its services inside of the infrastructure.

35
00:02:37,580 --> 00:02:43,160
For that purpose, I am going to right click dependencies, Add Project Reference and select the ordering

36
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:45,740
application and click the okay button.

37
00:02:46,610 --> 00:02:52,580
You can see that we have successfully added ordering application project getting reference in the ordering

38
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:53,600
infrastructure.

39
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:57,080
Lastly, we will go to the ordering API project.

40
00:02:57,080 --> 00:03:03,440
In ordering API we will add a project reference both ordering infrastructure and ordering application.

41
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:09,470
If you right click the dependencies Add Project reference, I'm going to select Ordering Application

42
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:12,440
and Ordering Infrastructure and click the okay button.

43
00:03:12,770 --> 00:03:18,590
If you double click the ordering API, you can see the item group comes in here from the ordering application

44
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:21,350
infrastructure reference to ordering API.

45
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:28,250
This allows the API layer to use application services and infrastructure implementations inside of the

46
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:28,700
endpoint.

47
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:29,600
Definitions.

48
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:35,780
After adding all necessary references, we can build the solution and ensure everything is correctly

49
00:03:35,780 --> 00:03:38,030
set up and there is no missing dependencies.

50
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:44,960
If you right click the ordering API and build the API project, you can see that will is succeeded completed.

51
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:49,790
That means we have successfully added project references into our clean architecture layers.

